24. Bellerophon, ordered by the king of Lycia, to destroy the monster Chimaera, is said to have done so by the help of the winged horse Pegasus. Chimaera was really a mountain in Lycia from which flames were always issuing. The ancient conception of it was a female monster with the head of a lion, the waist of a goat, and the tail of a serpent.
